  "texts": [
    "Photodissociation of HCN via HCN + h𝜈 → CN + H is enhanced in the dayside model, leading to enhanced HCN depletion compared to both the global terminator and 1D models.",
    "The latter two rely solely on the reversible H 2 + CN ⇌ H + HCN and HCN + H + M ⇌ H 2 CN + M reactions, as in subplot B, resulting in higher HCN abundances at low pressures.",
    "The presence of photolytic destruction in the dayside case, partially offset by H 2 CN + H → HCN + H 2, introduces a key divergence from the more shielded regions represented in subplot B.",
    "We present four comparison cases in Figure 10.",
    "Figure 10A shows the transmission spectra computed under chemical equilibrium for (i) a full 1D model, (ii) a 3D GCM (GA) with 1D chemical profiling and 1D radiative transfer, and (iii) a 3D GCM (ETA and WTA averages) with 1D chemical profiling and 3D radiative transfer and (iv) a 3D GCM (DA) with 1D chemical profiling and 3D radiative transfer, using the T-P profiles shown in Figure 5."
